# Keep the container build context small.
#
# The only image (claude/docker/Dockerfile) builds the `basecamp` Python tool,
# which needs src/, claude/, pyproject.toml, and uv.lock — nothing else. Anything
# else in the working tree would otherwise be tarred up and sent to the engine on
# every build, so it is excluded here.

# Virtualenvs, dependencies, VCS, caches
.venv/
node_modules/
.git/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.playwright-mcp/
**/__pycache__/

# Legacy Pi extension + pre-rearchitecture layout leftovers. These are gone from
# the repo, but can linger untracked in a working tree that predates the Pi
# deprecation, so they're excluded defensively to keep a stale checkout from
# bloating the build context.
pi/
core/
workspace/
pi-ui/
pi-git/
pi-tasks/
pi-swarm/
pi-browser/
pi-companion/
pi-engineering/
pi-bash-reviewer/

# Docs / tests / misc not needed to build the basecamp tool
docs/
tests/
migrations/
